  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis of a variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` describes one axis of a variable font, as returned by
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters>. It specifies the axis tag,
the minimum, default, and maximum values, and whether the axis should be hidden from
user-facing interfaces.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var axes = typeface.VariationDesignParameters;
foreach (var axis in axes)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"{axis.Tag}: min={axis.Min} def={axis.Default} max={axis.Max}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
